.\" Man page for ocode mcp
.TH OCODE-MCP 1 "June 2025" "ocode" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ocode-mcp \- Manage MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ocode mcp
\fIcommand\fR [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers. MCP servers provide additional
tools and resources to the agent.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBadd \fI<name>\fR
Add an MCP server (interactive wizard).
.TP
\fBlist\fR, \fBls\fR
List all MCP servers with status.
.TP
\fBauth \fI<name>\fR
Trigger OAuth flow for a remote server.
.TP
\fBauth list\fR
List OAuth-capable servers.
.TP
\fBlogout \fI<name>\fR
Clear stored OAuth tokens.
.TP
\fBdebug \fI<name>\fR
Diagnose connection issues.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show this help message and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List MCP servers:
.B ocode mcp list
.TP
Add a new MCP server:
.B ocode mcp add myserver
.TP
Authenticate with a remote server:
.B ocode mcp auth myserver
.TP
Debug connection:
.B ocode mcp debug myserver
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ocode (1)